# cron template for the {{CODENAME}} oracle headless loop harness (Linux).
#
# This is a TEMPLATE. It is rendered by scheduler/install_schedule.sh, which
# substitutes:
#   {{CODENAME}}      -> the oracle codename
#   {{ORACLE_ROOT}}   -> the ABSOLUTE oracle root directory
#   {{PYTHON}}        -> the python3 interpreter to use
#
# SAFETY:
#   * DISABLED BY DEFAULT. The active schedule line below is COMMENTED OUT with
#     a leading '#'. install_schedule.sh installs it commented unless run with
#     --enable, in which case it uncomments exactly this one line. Without
#     --enable nothing is ever scheduled.
#   * harness.py --once checks the kill-switch first and runs only allowlisted
#     loops under the autonomy gate, so the schedule is inert until
#     Meta.nosync/Autonomy/autonomy.yml turns autonomy ON.
#   * Output is redirected into the oracle's own tmp.nosync so logs stay inside
#     the sovereign tree.
#
# Schedule: top of every hour; harness.py decides what is actually due.
#
# m h dom mon dow command
#0 * * * * cd {{ORACLE_ROOT}} && {{PYTHON}} {{ORACLE_ROOT}}/_tools/harness.py --once >> {{ORACLE_ROOT}}/tmp.nosync/loops.harness.cron.log 2>&1
